                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "I currently use xmonad as my window manager.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "This like a few other tiling window managers, automatically\nchooses the size of new windows.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "I also use the Firefox option of restoring all my previous tabs when opening\nthe web browser.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "Let's say I have my browser occupying approximately 1/4 of the screen and then I close it.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "Later I reopen it,\nand my window manager chooses to make it fullscreen.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "Iceweasel appears to have persisted the size information,\nand despite the fact that the Iceweasel window is fullscreen, only the top left 1/4 of the window is actually\nfunctional.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "Resizing the window causes Iceweasel to realise the window isn't the size it thinks and then\nbehaviour is normal.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "I can reproduce this behaviour on a completely clean user account on my machine.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "However, I cannot reproduce\non the upstream 3.5.6 32-bit binary download from upstream.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": true
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": true, 
                    "text": "I believe this problem only started when 3.5\nmigrated into testing.", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
                {
                    "is_in_lex_summary": false, 
                    "text": "", 
                    "is_in_email_summary": false
                }, 
